=== Climate ===
Belgium has a mostly [[oceanic climate]], but the Belgian [[Ardennes (forest)|Ardennes]] has a [[continental climate]]. 

The highest temperature ever recorded in Belgium was {{cvt|41.8|C|F}}, on 25 July 2019 in [[Begijnendijk]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.vrt.be/vrtnws/nl/2019/07/26/hitte-zo-uitzonderlijk-was-het-gisteren/ | title=Zo uitzonderlijk was het gisteren: 41,8 graden in Begijnendijk, vandaag wat minder warm en kans op onweer | date=July 26, 2019 }}</ref> The lowest temperature ever recorded in Belgium was {{cvt|-30.1|C|F}}, on 20 January 1940 in [[Lesse]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Januari - KMI|url=http://www.meteo.be/meteo/view/nl/1119603-Januari.html|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811163445/http://www.meteo.be/meteo/view/nl/1119603-Januari.html|archive-date=2018-08-11|access-date=2023-02-12}}</ref>

== Politics ==
[[File:Koning Filip van België.jpg|thumb|230x230px|[[Philippe of Belgium]], current King.]]
Since 1993, Belgium is a [[federation|federal]] state, divided into three regions and three communities.

Regions:
* [[Brussels-Capital Region]]
* [[Flemish Region]] (or Flanders)
* [[Walloon Region]] (or Wallonia)

Communities:
* [[Flemish Community]]
* [[French Community of Belgium]]
* [[German-speaking Community of Belgium]]

It has a system of [[government]] known as a [[constitutional monarchy]], meaning that it has a [[monarch]], but that the monarch does not rule the country, and that a government is elected [[Democracy|democratically]].

Belgium has had its own monarchy since 1831. King [[Albert II of Belgium|Albert II]] left the throne on July 21, 2013 and the current king is [[Philippe of Belgium|Philippe]].

In Belgium, the government is elected. Between mid-2010 and late 2011, after no clear result in the [[election]], Belgium had no official government, until [[Elio Di Rupo]] became [[Prime Minister]]. [[Flanders]] and [[Wallonia]] both also have their own regional governments, and there is a notable independence movement in Flanders. [[Alexander De Croo]] is currently the Prime Minister.
